Такое понятие иммиграции как бремени и проблемы может быть избирательным активом, однако оно является экономически весьма дорогостоящим.
As the economists Ian Goldin and Geoffrey Cameron, remind us in a recent book summarizing the most recent knowledge of immigration (Exceptional People: How Migration Shaped Our World and Will Define Our Future, mai 2011, Princeton University Press, 352 pp.), there is wide consensus among specialists on the positive impact of migration flows on economic growth, wages and employment in countries, which admit immigrants.
